Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.76,0:30:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work of all the of everyone\Nlifts all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.39,0:31:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the karmic inheritance is we keep\Ndiscovering new cures for new things all
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.12,0:31:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the time. And I have a couple of\Npatients who have never recovered from a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.52,0:31:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of simple things. And I tell him,\Nat the rate at which the pharmaceutical
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.91,0:31:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,industry is pouring money into these\Ndiscoveries, don't forget the discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.12,0:31:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of any single common ailment is worth\Nmulti-millions, if not billions of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.60,0:31:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,dollars, you can be sure they're going\Nto find a cure for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.67,0:31:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so just hang on until the cure\Nappears. So I try to energize that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.24,0:31:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,thought form that a cure for whatever\Nyou're not recovered from so far will
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.64,0:31:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,appear will appear. So that's how things\Nappear, aren't they? They held they're
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.39,0:31:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,held as a possibility in human\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.76,0:31:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,out of\Nout of compassion for the suffering of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.15,0:31:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind and that in that way they tend\Nto manifest. So the doctors in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.39,0:31:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,audience remember most of the things you\Ndon't see syphilis anymore people
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.88,0:31:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting in line for injections with\Narsenic.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.08,0:32:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh they used to be lined up around the\Ncorner, the veterans arsenic shots and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.44,0:32:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,other doctors\Nfor hopeless syphilis and um General
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.00,0:32:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Parises of the Insane was the first\Nmental disorder I had treated at the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.72,0:32:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Milwaukee County Asylum for the Insane.\NIt was called It was called the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.08,0:32:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Milwaukee County Asylum for the Insane.\NThat was the name of it. They didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.20,0:32:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,deal in euphemisms in those days.\NAnd I told you I also interned at the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.55,0:32:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hospital for the Ruptured and Crippled\Nin Brooklyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.32,0:32:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the name of it. Hospital of\Nruptured and crippled.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.84,0:32:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, there wasn't this uh\Nfeeling uncomfortable neurotic
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.84,0:32:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sensitivity that pervades people now.\NYou know, they can't mention if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.96,0:32:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,male or female or if you're short or\Nlong or what your religion is or how far
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.03,0:32:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you went in school, all those things.\NSomebody's going to get feel
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.76,0:32:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,uncomfortable about it, you know.\NThere's a book out and I'll call
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.08,0:33:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,something the thought police anyway\Ntells you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.44,0:33:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,how these big publishing houses screen\Nespecially in the academic world
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.03,0:33:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that might be taken as\Noffensive by anybody. So their books are
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.67,0:33:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,getting smaller and smaller\Nfind that be four or five pages because
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.24,0:33:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,something everywhere is going to make\Nsomebody nervous. You see that is really
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.88,0:33:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,your problem and to project it onto\Nsociety of course is one of the great uh
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.27,0:33:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,less integrous movements of current\Nsociety. You know if something makes me
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.96,0:33:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uncomfortable we have to remove God from\Nany mention in society because it makes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.20,0:33:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,some people uncomfortable.\NNever dawn on them that removing God
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.00,0:33:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from any reference in society makes me\Nuncomfortable. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.55,0:33:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that removing it makes 70% of\Nthe population uncomfortable doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.20,0:33:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,dawn on the egocentric person who says\Nbecause it makes me comfortable. All
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.91,0:33:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,street cars should be removed from the\Nstreets. All buses should stop. Train
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.44,0:34:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,whistle should stop.\NBecause it makes me uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.64,0:34:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The people that are made uncomfortable\Nby the factual events in society need a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.20,0:34:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrist. That's what we're for.\NThat's what we're for, folks. If it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.63,0:34:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you uncomfortable, call us up.\NDon't forget, psychiatrists make a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.07,0:34:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of people uncomfortable, and I'm sure\Nthey would like to.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.32,0:34:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, people who don't see\Npsychiatrist and need to make a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.72,0:34:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,other people uncomfortable. So\Nwhat makes me uncomfortable is people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.56,0:34:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who are made uncomfortable.\NI feel very uncomfortable about people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.59,0:34:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that are always uncomfortable\Nbecause you know you're going to make
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.35,0:34:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,them uncomfortable. It's just a matter\Nof time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.48,0:34:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Even mentioning that there's people who\Nare made uncomfortable by everything
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.28,0:35:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,already makes them uncomfortable and\Nthey're going to complain and ask for a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.76,0:35:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,new law to block people from making\Nreferences to people who get
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.96,0:35:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,uncomfortable\Nbecause to do so makes them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.40,0:35:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,uncomfortable. You understand? So we end\Nup into this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.68,0:35:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,nonsensility\Nwhich keeps the trial lawyers societies
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.48,0:35:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,going.\NSo we have some questions and hopefully
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.72,0:35:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,some answers.\N>> What is the cause of addiction chemical
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.11,0:35:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and behavioral? And what is the\Nsolution?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.32,0:35:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good god.\NThe answer to that is uh you have to go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.64,0:35:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to an Elanon meeting and they'll tell\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.68,0:35:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's genetic karmic has to do with\Nbrain chemistry has to do with genes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.92,0:35:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,both addiction and depression t are\Ngenetically linked a family with a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.16,0:36:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of depression also usually that has a\Ngood deal of addiction in it and they're
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,very often crossed and\Nuh you know having treated 10,000
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.32,0:36:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,alcoholics And uh I knew Bill Wilson\Nback many years ago and then ran a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.52,0:36:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,clinic in the east where we treated tens\Nof thousands literally
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.72,0:36:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nand in uh out here one day a week. I
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.04,0:36:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,spent all day one day a week for 10\Nyears treating addiction. So from that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.68,0:36:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential background, one can say\Nthere certainly seems to be a genetic
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.88,0:36:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,disorder. It certainly runs in families\Nand it's certainly a lifestyle and it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.32,0:36:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly the the rate of addiction\Nincreases as your ancestors come closer
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.44,0:36:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and closer to the North Pole.\NIf your ancestors come from Scandinavia,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.64,0:36:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood is extremely higher than\Nif they come from Italy or Spain or the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.32,0:36:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mediterranean. So there's genetic,\Nethnic, I'm sure there's karmic reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.16,0:37:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people I know a number of\Npeople who died of alcoholism one death
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.64,0:37:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,after another and finally they came\Nback. Yeah, I know of one and the sixth
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.48,0:37:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,round of a lifetime of addiction. They\Nfinally surrendered it to God and became
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.72,0:37:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,sober. Don't forget sobriety was not\Naccomplishable before the 1940s.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.32,0:37:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever recovered from alcoholism.\NAnd when they did, they were such an
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.40,0:37:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,oddity that they were written up as sort\Nof a medical oddity. And
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.92,0:37:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we owe the recovery from addiction to\Nthe humility of the Swiss psychoanalyst
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.52,0:37:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Young. Because when Roland, who was\Nwellto-do, went to see Carl Young in
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.20,0:37:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Switzerland for psychoanalysis,\Nhe finally stopped drinking and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.59,0:37:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,went back to America. After a short\Ntime, Roland got drunk again and became
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.92,0:37:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,severely depressed and he went back to\Nsee Carl Young in Switzerland and Young
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.92,0:38:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,think we all are thankful for his\Nhumility. He said, "Alas, unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.80,0:38:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,neither my art nor my science can be of\Nhelp to you. However, it has been
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.11,0:38:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,reported from time to time throughout\Nhistory that there are those who have
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.04,0:38:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,thrown themselves wholeheartedly into\Nsome spiritual organization and they
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.56,0:38:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have recovered. I think at the time was\Nan atheist. So it was not exactly great
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.44,0:38:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,news.\NRoland came back to America and he
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.88,0:38:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered the group uh that uh formed\Nthe essence of the 12 steps of AA. I
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.24,0:38:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,forget what the name of the group was at\Nthe time
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.59,0:38:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and Roland threw himself wholeheartedly\Ninto this spiritual group to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.56,0:38:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,everything to God and to\Nhonestly honestly etc. what became I
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.16,0:38:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,think they were at that time only eight\Nsteps. They became eventually 12 and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.28,0:38:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Roland conveyed this to Evie who\Nrecovered and Evie then gave the message
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.07,0:39:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to Bill W.\Nwho u scoffed at it and said it was
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.80,0:39:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ridiculous\Nbecause Bill was an atheist and he was
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.28,0:39:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not ready to hear anything about the god\Nbusiness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.56,0:39:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and he told Ebby don't come back about\Nthis god business and uh and then Bill
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.20,0:39:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,had a great black despair and he\Nlistened to what Evie had said and being
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.52,0:39:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,an atheist at the time he surrendered to\Nonly what he could assume would be God
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.83,0:39:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and then went through a profound\Ntransformation in which The room lit up
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.16,0:39:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with a holy light.\NThe energy field of that moment has
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.80,0:39:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,saved millions of lives and will save\Nmillion more. So that one instant which
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.32,0:39:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I never calibrated but it's obviously\Nover 700 or so radiated out through all
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.35,0:39:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of society. So you see what I say that\Neach one who reaches a high low, Bill W
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.59,0:40:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,himself who an atheist suddenly went\Ninto the presence and through him
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.28,0:40:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,radiated sufficient energy for millions\Nof people to recover from hopeless
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.76,0:40:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,diseases of all kinds. And of course the\Nbasic principles of spiritual honesty
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.07,0:40:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are now utilized in many of man's\Ndisorders from anger management from
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.04,0:40:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,child molestation\Nuh to all kinds of acts of brutality and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.40,0:40:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,hopeless sociological\Ndisorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.35,0:40:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the person who enters a 12step\Ngroup is really hoping for is the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.04,0:40:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous\Nand hope and because cal aa calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.44,0:40:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at 540\Nthe miraculous is quite possible and it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.40,0:40:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,happens with sufficient frequency that\Nit's become the greatest organization of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.48,0:41:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,its kind in history.\NIt's the energy field of AA that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.52,0:41:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 540. So once the person\Nattends the meeting and and links up
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.07,0:41:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,psychically with the group they recover\Nthey recover because of the field. The
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.80,0:41:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,person himself is probably about 140\N140 but the field is 540. So as long
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.28,0:41:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he's so he's sustained by the field. So\Nbut that is not his own level of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.64,0:41:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. It's a borrowed level. So\Nhe's under the protective umbrella of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.48,0:41:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the group karma, the group\Nconsciousness. So long as he stays
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.24,0:41:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,aligned and committed with the group,\Nthe sobriety persists without any energy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.96,0:41:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or effort. Person never even thinks of a\Ndrink. Life is smooth, beautiful. Then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.40,0:41:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego comes back and says, "You don't\Nneed a anymore." And therefore, he walks
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.20,0:41:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,away from the 540.\NIf the energy fueled of the recovered
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.52,0:41:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,person is over 540, he doesn't need to\Ngo to meetings anymore. But if it's
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.83,0:42:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,under 540, which is the great likelihood\Nprobably 99.9% of the time, The minute
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.96,0:42:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he walks away from the group, he\Nrelapses and now the agony is worse. So
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.00,0:42:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because the more advanced you are\Nspiritually, the more grave is the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.31,0:42:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of a mistake.\N>> As one progresses spiritually, how does
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.80,0:42:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,one distinguish revelation from ego\Ncreations?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.59,0:42:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Ego creation. Well, revelation is a\Npeculiar experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.35,0:42:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh it's like advanced intuition in a\Nway.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.16,0:42:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nonverb. First of all, it's\Nnonverbal. The ego verbalizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.07,0:42:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nonverbal knowingness which\Narises spontaneously from the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.68,0:42:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a knowingness. It's g n o s i s.\NIt arises from the field. From the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.44,0:43:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's arising from here. From here. It\Narises in form in logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.24,0:43:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness has no words to it.\NOne time in walking out in the field
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.31,0:43:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there suddenly came out of nowhere\Nbecause there was no thinking about it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.16,0:43:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,like the revelation of the totality of\Nhuman suffering throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.44,0:43:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of the all of it, allness\Nof it of such immense dimension that it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.52,0:43:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be described even at this moment.\NJust it was the knowingness of it like a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.35,0:43:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,great overwhelming\Nrecall those things before a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.52,0:43:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A knowingness that revealed itself in\Nthat moment. this intense devote because
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.07,0:43:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was\Nan intensed Christian,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.52,0:43:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,an acolyte,\Nvoice, soprano, all the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.40,0:44:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly\Nthe belief in God went
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.72,0:44:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,disappeared just like that.\Nany god that could allow the totality of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.44,0:44:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that\Nbecause I thought God created that. So I
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.92,0:44:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,held God responsible for the total agony\Nof the creation of the collective
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.80,0:44:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness of the ego.\NA grave spiritual mistake. And that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.83,0:44:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness that it was the ego that\Ncreated the total suffering of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.72,0:44:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and not God\Nwas like telepathically transmitted. And
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.83,0:44:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in that moment, the patient got up and\Nstood and walked away like normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.04,0:44:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the nurses and all would faint when\Nthey saw all this kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.92,0:44:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was neither purposeful nor\Nintention nor was there any
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.59,0:44:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,verbalization.\NIn that case the bringing forth of that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.35,0:45:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness was itself spontaneous and\Nnonverbal. There was no verbalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.88,0:45:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like the presentation of a\Npicture and the patients own spirit saw
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.76,0:45:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the picture and forgave God and\Ncame out of hell because when they came
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.88,0:45:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in they were in hell.\NIt was their moment of salvation from
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.07,0:45:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,hell.\NSo realization revelation occurs of its
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.24,0:45:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,own energy. It's a presentation. It\Ncomes to you. It's not something you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.83,0:45:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,seek and find.\NIt's like a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.59,0:45:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a gift. One can take no\Ncredit for it because you were thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.31,0:45:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,about squirrels maybe at the moment and\Nall of a sudden all of that disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.40,0:45:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the infinite presence of God reveals\Nitself as though everything
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.31,0:46:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is turned on to the technical and three\Ndimension and the significance and the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.88,0:46:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning and the reality of that which it\Nis because all stands forth as an
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.59,0:46:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,expression of God.\Ncomes forth of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.83,0:46:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If it comes from the ego, there's a\Nthinkingness that precedes it or
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.20,0:46:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,accompanies it. Or there's a\Nverbalization, all which I've just said,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.11,0:46:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I put into words. But the experience of\Nit is totally wordless.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.16,0:46:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you look at the beauty of a\Nsetting sun, there's no words about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.40,0:46:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, anything you can say about it\Nis enormous detraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.04,0:46:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a total experience of stunning\Nbeauty which has no words for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.68,0:46:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What is a parent's responsibility and\Nwhat can parents do in guiding their
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.20,0:46:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,children about uh the violence and video\Ngames and TV and all of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.80,0:46:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's a tough one.\N>> I am very glad I don't have children
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.40,0:47:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,right now.\N>> Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.24,0:47:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Society is being attacked in two\Ndimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.76,0:47:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only the spiritual power of groups\Nsuch like such as this to prevent it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.76,0:47:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from being destroyed.\NIt gets it from the luciferic by the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.88,0:47:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,distortion of logic and reason and\Nmisrepresentation
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.88,0:47:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of facts and demonization of that which\Nis integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.64,0:47:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as we saw this morning when we\Ncalibrated some of those things. It gets
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.96,0:47:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it from the satanic energy\Nwhich is that of violence, seduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.11,0:47:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,rape, beheading people, serial murder,\Nthe joy of killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.20,0:48:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sometimes expressed quite subtly. I\Nwas quite dismayed to find a new woman's
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.00,0:48:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,group called B.\NAnd the purpose of the group was to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.48,0:48:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,learn how to go out in the field with\Nshotguns and kill feeasants and be just
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.56,0:48:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,like men.\NThe number of fallacies involved there
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.16,0:48:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is stacked upon each other. See,\Nfirst of all, they picked if that is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.20,0:48:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,supposedly masculine,\Nit's lowest expression. If you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.76,0:48:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,be like a man, don't pick his lowest\Ndenominator. Try to pick the highest.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.31,0:48:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They picked the lowest denominator\Nbecause the women were enjoying the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.16,0:48:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,death of the feeasants. In fact, they're\Npracticing holding the feeasant in it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.55,0:48:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,their hands as it took 15 minutes to die\Nand sharing the experience of feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.88,0:48:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,its squirming death spasms. I thought\Nthis is manly grotesque, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.00,0:48:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,really grotesque\Nand cloaked on the idea of first of all
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.83,0:48:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that the feminine is inferior to the\Nmasculine which is bizarre and a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.31,0:49:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,delusional distortion of truth to begin\Nwith.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.24,0:49:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhy rise above that which you are not?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.07,0:49:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a false\Nstraw man to begin with. In the world I
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.04,0:49:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,grew up, nobody ever considered a woman\Nless than a man that I ever noticed. You
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.07,0:49:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,said anything disrespectful in front of\Nyour grandmother. God help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.00,0:49:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you who ranked in the home.\NFrank. Frank don't your the drapes. My
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.00,0:49:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,grandfather walked through and he hide\Nhis pipe like this. He walk through the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.35,0:49:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,living room. My grandmother would be\Nafter Frank, Frank, the drapes. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.96,0:49:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,she'd wave the drapes and she'd want the\Nsmoke in the drapes. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.83,0:49:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he was confined to his smoking room. You\Nknow what I'm saying? So, the illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.96,0:49:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was a socioeconomic distortion because\Nshe wasn't out in the workplace. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.11,0:49:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,she wasn't supposed to be out in the\Nworkplace. You died of shame if your
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.00,0:49:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,wife had to go to work. And I don't know\Nif a single woman's interest in their
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.35,0:50:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,job. She feel very badly for the poor\Nold Spinster lady who has to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.80,0:50:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we grew into that which was the\Nsocial expectation of the time. Each one
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.16,0:50:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of us perfectly fulfilled whatever was\Nthe expectation of the time. One thing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.55,0:50:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was not better than another. What was\Nthe question?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.68,0:50:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Huh?\N>> Are you going to tell our
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.31,0:50:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> what?\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.59,0:50:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea.\N>> So, I don't know. Maybe maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.11,0:50:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> is a calibration that you come into the\Nworld with the one you left in your last
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.64,0:50:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,incarnation.\N>> I never asked that. Um I would assume
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.52,0:50:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that you spent some time in the inner\Nplanes
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.04,0:50:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and could have made some progress there.\NI don't know. I never asked that. I
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.24,0:50:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,don't even know if we have permission to\Nask that. Uh let's see. We have
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.76,0:51:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,permission to ask that in public.\NOkay. Between lifetimes, one has the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.88,0:51:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity for spiritual advancement.\NResistance. I guess we have the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.20,0:51:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity for spiritual advancement.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.80,0:51:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\N>> What does healthy sexuality look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.20,0:51:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Look like\NLooks like a lot of fun if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.72,0:51:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People wonder what sexuality calibrates.\NIt calibrates about 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.48,0:51:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, money calibrates 20 around. So it\Nseems that that which is necessary for
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.96,0:51:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,physical survival and the expression of\Nphysicality and having a human body such
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.11,0:52:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as eating and things like this\Ncalibrated at a rather neutral level
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.11,0:52:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,like 200 to 205.\NThe reason it has a bad reputation in
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.35,0:52:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,certain spiritual groups is what they\Nmean is the attachment to it. The
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.48,0:52:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment being run by it. Being run by\Nthat energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.24,0:52:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nas an expression of devotion and love.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.55,0:52:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The mutual experience of pleasure is\Nnothing but you might say
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.16,0:52:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a beneficence to each other like a\Nblessing to each other or reaffirmation
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.83,0:52:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of\Nloving each other. You say intimacy and
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.59,0:52:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,closeness when it becomes a pursuit\Ndriven driving a person then you're
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.64,0:52:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,being run by it. So anything collecting\Nantiques is the same. You can be run by
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.92,0:53:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it, you know, collecting pancakes.\N>> Collecting old tools. Well, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.48,0:53:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Collecting old tools can also be in a\Nsession.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.07,0:53:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you can hardly get in the\Ntool room. All these wonderful old
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.04,0:53:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,antique tools, you know.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.16,0:53:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so these things are amusements, they're\Nproclivities, they're hobbies.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.31,0:53:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the traditional view is um\Nthat the downside of anything is one's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.40,0:53:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment to it and the ascribing of\Nmagical qualities to that which is which
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.76,0:53:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is not so. It's only a projection, a\Nglamorization. So what we see is the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.07,0:53:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,glamorization and the exploitation of\Nsexuality
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.64,0:53:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a different story than actual\Nsexuality. Yeah. Sexuality is certainly
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.04,0:54:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a delightful pleasure without which\Nthere would be no human beings on the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.88,0:54:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,planet\Nbe the end of the race. So I guess it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.40,0:54:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,must be okay or we wouldn't be here.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.07,0:54:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Created by God. And uh the physicality\Nthen is merely the expression of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.00,0:54:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,um a physical craving or an emotional\Ncommitment. So it can be one of many
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.52,0:54:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,things.\NAnd of course everything is the karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.92,0:54:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of everything is determined\Nby the spiritual intention behind it. So
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.83,0:54:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't the sexuality, it's the\Nspiritual intention behind it. To
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.48,0:54:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,exploit the weak, to take advantage of\Npeople, to slip on sleeping pills and
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.20,0:54:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have violent sex with them while they're\Nunconscious are obviously
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.04,0:54:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,severe perversions of what should be a\Nnatural instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.24,0:54:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. And people in spiritual work go\Nthrough a couple of things. It's first
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.68,0:54:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,comes vegetarianism and then the next\Ncomes celibacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.76,0:55:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think celibacy and vegetarianism\Nare wonderful and you should do them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.48,0:55:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did everybody leave the room?\NIt's because of its meaning to you. If
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.52,0:55:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you think that you're killing, you see,\Nif you believe in death, then you think
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.76,0:55:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that this animal is being killed for you\Nand now you can't eat an animal because
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.48,0:55:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you believe in death. You think it just\Ndied.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.64,0:55:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Same with sexuality if you think it's\Nevil and etc etc. So these things as you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.31,0:55:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,evolve u in consciousness have different\Nmeanings and significance. So you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.31,0:55:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,say anything's right or wrong. You can\Nsay does it serve your spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.68,0:55:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,progress at this point or does it not\Nserve it. There may be a point at which
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.31,0:55:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel guilty about sex and it's not\Nserving it. However then you have to get
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.44,0:55:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,off the guilt about the sexuality. So\Nthe same with thinking that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.64,0:56:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,killing things in order to in order to\Neat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.44,0:56:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing feeasants for fun is like\Nshooting prairie dogs for fun. I think
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.59,0:56:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a perversion of the sporting\Ninstinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.79,0:56:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, like every other animal has sort of\Nan innate desire to kill things. And
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.24,0:56:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's one of the things we transcend.\NWhen you think that 40 million
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.64,0:56:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Buffalo roam the plains and there's not\None left. Not one. You say out of 40
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.28,0:56:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,million. There's got to be one buffalo\Nsomewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.72,0:56:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We hunted all over Sedona. We didn't\Nfind one. All over Yeapai County, all
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.64,0:56:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,over Arizona.\NOut of 40 million magnificent creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.07,0:56:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Man did not leave even one. No, not one\Nwild buffalo love. Not one.
